                  , on the <rs id="t17750218-6-cd24" type="crimeDate">16th of January</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17750218-6-off23 t17750218-6-cd24"></join>, about the hour of eight in the night, and stealing eleven pair of worsted stockings, value twenty shillings the property of the said Elizabeth, in her dwelling house
            </rs> ++.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17750218-6-person112">
                  Elizabeth
                   Platt
               <interp inst="t17750218-6-person112" type="surname" value="Platt"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person112" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person112" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t17750218-6-viclabel25" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17750218-6-victim111 t17750218-6-viclabel25"></join> and <rs id="t17750218-6-viclabel26" type="occupation">hosier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17750218-6-victim111 t17750218-6-viclabel26"></join>, on the 6th of January, about Eleven<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177502180027"></xptr> o'clock, I was up stairs with a few friends, hearing the cry thieves, I ran down and found a pane of glass in the shop broke, a hat dashed through and eleven pair of stockings taken out, they were tied up in a paper with my mark upon them, my servant was gone in pursuit of the thieves.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17750218-6-person113">
                  John
                   Keaps
               <interp inst="t17750218-6-person113" type="surname" value="Keaps"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person113" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person113" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Last Monday three weeks our window was broke, I ran to the door and saw the prisoner run across the street, I pursued him and cried stop thief, in consequence of that he was stopped and the bundle of stockings was found at his feet.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17750218-6-person114">
                  Ann
                   Mascall
               <interp inst="t17750218-6-person114" type="surname" value="Mascall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person114" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person114" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sitting at work behind the compter, I heard the window break, I got up and took hold of a parcel, a man put his hand through the window and took the parcel from me, I don't know the person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17750218-6-person115">
                  Joseph
                   Smith
               <interp inst="t17750218-6-person115" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person115" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17750218-6-person115" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner drop the stockings from under his coat when Keaps had hold of him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I know nothing of it, I was walking along there was a cry stop thief, the man that stopped me first said I was not the man and let me go again.</p>
               <p>He called four witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17750218-6-verdict27" type="verdictDescription">
